## **3. SEO-Friendly Product Page HTML**  
**File**: `index.html` for `codeximmortal.com/blockchain`  

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <meta name="description" content="Secure, blockchain-based donation platform for faith communities with GDPR compliance and open-source smart contracts." />
  <meta name="keywords" content="blockchain donation, faith communities, smart contracts, open-source, GDPR compliance" />
  <title>Blockchain for Faith Communities | Codex Immortal</title>
</head>
<body>
  <header>
    <h1>Blockchain Platform for Faith-Based Charitable Giving</h1>
    <p>Transparent, immutable, and GDPR-compliant donation tracking using Ethereum smart contracts.</p>
  </header>

  <section>
    <h2>Features</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Ethereum Contracts:</strong> Open-source donation tracking (MIT License)</li>
      <li><strong>GDPR Compliance:</strong> Audit logs for all transactions</li>
      <li><strong>Frontend App:</strong> React + Ethers.js for real-time tracking</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>How It Works</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>Donors send ETH via Ethereum.</li>
      <li>Smart contracts log donations and cause categories (ISO 3166 standard).</li>
      <li>Admins withdraw funds to verified charities using only-admin modifiers.</li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <footer>
    <p>© 2024 Codex Immortal. All rights reserved.</p>
    <a href="https://github.com/codeximmortal/blockchain-for-faith">GitHub: Open-Source Code</a>
  </footer>
</body>
</html>
```

